s an example, the proposed framework has been applied and the results show that the solution of the proposed framework is more responsive to the earthquake impact on railway system compared to topology-based methods. Note that the proposed framework can also be extended to identify pre-disaster investment plans for other transportation systems under natural disasters.","publicationCount":0,"publicationCountByYear":[],"citationCnt":2,"citationCountByYear":[],"rank":21146.0,"entityType":0},"dataVersion":"2019-01-11-prod"}